arrow_comments: seems generally fine. Arrow might be a little recognizable, but maybe not terrible?
wedge_comments: It's ok! This particular configuration feels a little "boring"
ushape_comments: I don't love this one because the base just seems very different than other base shapes in terms of convexness and thinness
tripod_comments: I like this base shape. The positioning of appendage 2 is weird - weight distribution wouldn't work! Maybe if it appeared somewhere or at the bottom of all tripod feet, it would be better
trefoil_comments: I don't love this one, base shape feels a little less substantial than others. I like appendage 1 but I worry it's more complex/ large than many others
torus_comments: Appendage 1 just seems a little disconnected from the others; appendages 3 and 4 are maybe too similar?
spiral_comments: This one's creative but I think the spiral is just too different compared to all of the other bases
sims_comments: kind of humanoid, doesn't feel very coherent as a whole
rock_comments: This is a super cool shape, but definitely more complex than some other bases. Appendages work but the positioning of 2 is weird - seems very cramped
pyramid_comments: this one seems good; appendages could be a little more prominent; is there a little base appendage at the bottom (the blue in the sketch)
pumpkin_comments: I think this generally seems good. Obviously the appendages aren't quite right yet (hanging in space)
prince_comments: I think it's generally ok, but maybe too similar to the other cylindric base shape (so we'd probably want to choose one). Definitely looks animate. Appendage 2 is a little more complex than others with multiple brances
plus_comments: I think it works ok but I find the appendages not terribly inspired here; hard to see the bottom appendage in the current angle, might feel a bit different if that were visible
pacman_comments: This one's not my favorite in terms of base shape, also pretty animate-looking. But in principle this would be ok
moon_comments: don't love this base shape; appendage 1 is just a little small + bland; appendage 2 is maybe also a bit small?
heart_comments: I think the carved our heart is just not our best base shape
gumdrop_comments: This matches an existing/old fribble type pretty closely. The appendages in principle seem good, but they seem a little small in general relative to the base size
frustum_comments: this guys fine but maybe a little boring/ simple? Also a little animate
diamond_comments: the base is cool, but also a bit more textured/ interesting than some of the other bases AND dependent on angle - so might depend on the full set
cylinder_comments: This is very similar to an existing fribble example. My only hesitation is that it looks a bit like a bird or fish with wings
crinkle_comments: I think this one is cool, but the current appendages make it seem very animate/ animal-like
bowtie_comments: appendage 1 isn't bad, it's just a little too close to a poop emoji for me : ) I think the base shape is pretty good too.
bowl_comments: looks a little like a little robot person
boot_comments: I think the boot is a little too much like a real object, maybe?

ushape_comments: appendage 2 just looks like a base/pedestal, not an appendage of the object
tripod_comments: appendage 1 placed where it is looks too much like a "head", and appendage 2 doesn't look like part of object (just a stand)
spiral_comments: this whole thing confuses me. is appendage 1 pink + blue? what is appendage 4?
sims_comments: appendage 2 (as labeled in right image) isn't on left object; is appendage 3 both orange and green parts, or are those 2 and 3?
pyramid_comments: appendage 3 doesn't match in both pictures (don't like blue appendage on left because looks like pedestal/plate, pegs on right are ok but seems like they should be same color)
pumpkin_comments: not sure what counts as each appendage because of mismatch between pictures. Base shape and appendage 2 ("stem") are ok on their own, but together it looks too much like pumpkin or other fruit. are blue and green shapes 1 appendage or 2?
prince_comments: base shape too much like a fish? and confused over appendages 3 and 4
plus_comments: something about appendage 4 bothers me (perhaps its just that you can't see all of it)
heart_comments: don't love base shape with weird cutout, but like the appendages
gumdrop_comments: appendage 4 just looks like pedestal (not part of object)
frustum_comments: this one like like an animal/animate object
diamond_comments: where is appendage 2? don't like this one in general
bowtie_comments: base shape looks like 2 separate shapes barely touching. Might like more if they were more connected. confused about appendages 3 and 4
bowl_comments: i like this one, but it might be because it looks like an animal (which might not be a good thing)
boot_comments: appendage 1 should only be used if crinkle fry base shape not used (too similar); worried that boot looks too much like familiar object (shoe, foot)

arrow_comments: More color contrast between appendages and the base would be good if we'd like it to be extra eyecatching.
wedge_comments: Appendages difficult to see and the shapes of appendages are similar
spiral_comments: Appendage 3 gets a little lost, but overall I really like this one.
pumpkin_comments: Pumpkin with less vegetal-like appendages would be more acceptable. As-is appendage 2 & 3 look like a stem and leaf enhancing the pumpkin-ness of it all. Also appendage 1 is floating in the rendered image..
prince_comments: Appendage 4 seems like an add-on to appendage 1 and not its own appendage.
pacman_comments: Angle of object might matter more for this one than others.
moon_comments: This is an odd banana...makes me think of peanut butter jelly time
heart_comments: This is a good example of how the appendages can take an identifiable shape and make it less easy to identify.
gumdrop_comments: This feels more subdued than other options.
crinkle_comments: I'd just change the color of appendage 1 to contrast with the base more.
boot_comments: Same comments as the pumpkin shape

ushape_comments: What if the appendage1 turned vertical?
rock_comments: Need to pay caution to keep the appendages suitable distance.
prince_comments: Not sure, but a little wired somehow.
frustum_comments: Maybe looks better if appendage1 have a bigger size.
diamond_comments: Maybe better if the ball of the appendage1 looks more smooth, e.g. softer peaks?

arrow_comments: For appendages 1 & 3, it would be better if they use different colors as the base object.
wedge_comments: It might be hard to find an angle where appendages 1, 2, & 4 are all clearly visible
ushape_comments: I am wondering if it might be possible to make the U shape less like a letter (e.g., making it fatter?)
tripod_comments: See previous comments for the number of colors and parts for an appendage.
trefoil_comments: This combination seems like a bird to me. I think this is because of the combination of appendages 1 & 4 and the base shape.
spiral_comments: It's hard to tell whether appendage 1 and base shape is more visually prominent in this combination. Appendage 1 also is more salient than any of the other appendages. Appendage 3 looks like two appendages instead of one.
rock_comments: It's a bit hard to tell what appendage 2 looks like based on the image here. From what I could see, it seems like a square? Appendage 2, to me, also feels more detached to the base object than the other ones. Appendage 1 also seems to be more complex than the other ones (in the sense that it has two parts and two colors).
pyramid_comments: Cannot see appendage 1 in the 3d image, and it seems to attach to another appendage instead of the base shape.
pumpkin_comments: For appendage 1, I am wondering if we could use just one part instead of having two. For appendage 2 & 3, it might be good if we move one of them to a different location so that they are not interfering with each other. For appendage 4, I think viewing from a horizontal angle would make it more visible.
prince_comments: For appendages 1 and 3, I am wondering if it might be helpful to have the parts that belong to the same appendage use the same color. This allows for 1) controlling the number of colors present in the image and 2) making the parts seem more integral
plus_comments: Appendage 4 is hard to see from this angle. For appendage 1, see previous comment regarding appendages with multiple parts.
pacman_comments: It might be helpful to put appendages 2 & 3 in different places. They currently seem to overlap with each other.
heart_comments: I think it might be hard to find an angle that makes all appendages visible.
frustum_comments: I think it might be enough to just use one part in appendage 3.
diamond_comments: I am wondering whether we would want to clarify what an appendage is. It could have been the angle, but appendage 1 in this picture seems to be attaching to another appendage (4) instead of being attached to the base shape.
cylinder_comments: For the base shape, it is hard to see the tilt from a top-down angle. Hard to see appendage 4 from this angle also.
crinkle_comments: For appendage 1, it might be helpful to use a different color than the base shape. For appendages 2 & 4, see comments from previous questions for number of parts and colors
bowtie_comments: It might be good to keep each appendage and the base shape distinct in its color.
bowl_comments: Appendage 2 is attaching to another appendage instead of attaching to the base shape. Appendage 3 are two parts not connected to each other, which is hard to say whether it counts as one or two appendage(s) and this might affect complexity. Appendage 4 is good but hard to see from the 3d object's angle.
boot_comments: I like all the appendages here. For appendage 2, it is less visible in the 3d image's angle compared to the 2d image. Appendage 2 may require a certain angle (horizontal view angle) in order to be the most visible.
additional_comments: Although some shapes are somewhat identifiable by themselves, the overall combinations are usually novel and do not look alike an item in real life. For appendages, I think it might be good to standardize: 1) how many parts it can have (only one part, or two parts are also allowed; my concern for having two parts is whether this will make complexity hard to interpret because then some appendages are more complex than the others); 2) number of colors and whether the color can be the same as the base object; 3) whether they can attach to the base object and/or other appendages; 4) maybe also size?

wedge_comments: appendages too small, base too pointy
spiral_comments: The concave core of the base is not great
pyramid_comments: The base shape makes the object too sharp
pumpkin_comments: The base looks good, but the appendages are very small
plus_comments: appendages too small, base is too pointy
moon_comments: base shape is weird and appendages are too small
diamond_comments: don't like the instability of the shape
cylinder_comments: I think the double appendages (e.g. #2 here) should count as 2. I can't see #4 in the rendered image
crinkle_comments: Looks a little bit like a weird animal

pumpkin_comments: App.4 does not look like the other appendages to me, bur rather like a platform to present it. Overall, it looks quite complex to me
moon_comments: App4 looks very small to me, overall this looks smaller/relatively thiin compared to the others (taking up less pixels)
crinkle_comments: I like this one a lot, I think app2 could be bigger
bowtie_comments: I think this is a great one, all appendages have roughly the same size and are relatively easy to distinguish/detect

pumpkin_comments: I'm not sure how clear appendeges 3 and 4 will look in the actual image we will use; they don't look visually prominenet with the pumpkin
crinkle_comments: I think appendage 3 might be too big for an appendage

arrow_comments: Will need to edit colors and think about two-part appendages, but otherwise pretty good.
wedge_comments: Appendage 1 is appropriate but very similar to an appendage on another image. I generally like this one, though.
ushape_comments: I like this, but the u-shape is quite a bit different from most other bases.
tripod_comments: There's something about the way the appendages "sit" on this base that makes it seem a little different from the others.
trefoil_comments: I really like this one in general. I think it could be rotated a little to make the bottom appendage more visible, but otherwise it seems good.
torus_comments: For whatever reason, I don't really like appendage 1. It's too big or something. I also am not sure about appendages that have two parts. We may just want to pick one of the parts.
spiral_comments: Like the u-shape, this is quite a bit different from other bases. Also, it seems maybe more like a bunch of appendages than a base and appendages. I do like the way it looks, though.
sims_comments: Again, unsure about two-part appendages. Also I don't love the way appendage 2 seems to cut the base, but maybe a different rotation would solve that.
rock_comments: Again, maybe this base is a little more "complex" than other bases. Appendage 1 is two parts but in a different way than others that appear to go "through" the base, and appendage 2 is like a strange big square, but it could maybe work with a different base.
pyramid_comments: This combo of appendages looks a little simple.
pumpkin_comments: I like this base and appendages, but I don't really like them all together. It looks too much like a pumpkin with the appendages at the top.
prince_comments: This looks like a submarine to me, but I think it could work with some tweaks. Appendage 3 is a two-part appendage too, but I think it would be okay if it was all one color.
plus_comments: I don't love this base shape, at least at this rotation, but I think it could be okay if it was a little more of a side view.
pacman_comments: I'd swap around the location of some of the appendages, but otherwise I think it's not bad.
moon_comments: I don't love this base with the big blob on the end that looks like it could be an appendage. It's also pretty close to another base shape (the teardrop-looking one) so I'd maybe choose one or the other.
heart_comments: This base is a maybe a little too familiar (but probably not more familiar than the bowl shape). Would need to be rotated to see appendage 1 if we kept it as-is.
gumdrop_comments: I like this one in general. I'd maybe rotate it slightly to see the bottom appendage better.
frustum_comments: This guy also looks a little more animate than some others. I think could work with minor tweaks, though.
diamond_comments: Diamond base shape is maybe a little more complex than other base shapes, so it might be one we can skip. Again, this has appendages attached to other appendages, and I'm not sure we want that.
cylinder_comments: I think this one is good. It seems like one of the most similar to the Tarr fribbles. It has a two-part appendage, but now I'm wondering if maybe that's okay as long as the parts are the same color?
crinkle_comments: I really like this base for whatever reason. There are a lot of two-part appendages here, and it looks animal-like, but I think it could work with some tweaks.
bowtie_comments: There is a lot going on with the multiple two-part appendages, but otherwise I think we could make some edits to make this completely appropriate.
bowl_comments: I think we need to consider whether it's okay to have appendages attached to appendages, as in this image. Also it has a two part appendage, which I'm not sure about. Otherwise, I think it's good with some minor edits.
